1
00:00:00,605 --> 00:00:02,906
CATHERINE: <i>Nine years ago I witnessed</i>
<i>my mother's murder.</i>

2
00:00:02,908 --> 00:00:06,749
<i>I would've been killed, too,</i>
<i>if it hadn't been for Vincent.</i>

3
00:00:06,849 --> 00:00:09,367
VINCENT: <i>I was part of an experimental</i>
<i>Special Forces group.</i>

4
00:00:09,369 --> 00:00:12,687
<i>Their goal was to create</i>
<i>the perfect super soldier.</i>

5
00:00:12,689 --> 00:00:14,739
<i>But something went wrong.</i>

6
00:00:14,741 --> 00:00:15,940
You're him.

7
00:00:15,942 --> 00:00:20,461
<i>Being in any relationship,</i>
<i>it's a risk.</i>

8
00:00:20,463 --> 00:00:23,298
Dr. Forbes, it's about
something that you wrote.

9
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,532
That was years ago.

10
00:00:24,534 --> 00:00:27,468
I have evidence that a
cross-species creature exists.

11
00:00:27,470 --> 00:00:29,220
I could do with a biochemist.

12
00:00:29,222 --> 00:00:31,689
I'd include you in all
aspects of the investigation.

13
00:00:31,691 --> 00:00:34,175
CATHERINE:
<i>My nurse, you might know her?</i>

14
00:00:34,177 --> 00:00:35,476
We grew up together.

15
00:00:35,478 --> 00:00:36,894
We were pretty close.

16
00:00:36,896 --> 00:00:37,895
They said you were dead.

17
00:00:37,897 --> 00:00:39,697
You should've
just given up on me.

18
00:00:39,699 --> 00:00:42,517
ALEX:
<i>I loved you.</i>

19
00:00:42,519 --> 00:00:45,103
CATHERINE:
Maybe I've been misreading us.

20
00:00:49,825 --> 00:00:51,442
(panting)

21
00:00:54,246 --> 00:00:55,496
(knock on door)

22
00:00:55,498 --> 00:00:57,065
Hi.

23
00:00:57,067 --> 00:00:59,567
Hey.

24
00:00:59,569 --> 00:01:01,402
Remind me never
to get shot again.

25
00:01:01,404 --> 00:01:02,453
Never get shot again.

26
00:01:02,455 --> 00:01:04,505
Come in.

27
00:01:04,507 --> 00:01:06,908
Thanks.

28
00:01:06,910 --> 00:01:10,578
Now put the
dumbbell down.

29
00:01:10,580 --> 00:01:12,246
Why do I get
the feeling

30
00:01:12,248 --> 00:01:14,098
that this is going
to hurt even worse?

31
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,351
Give me your hands.
Come on.

32
00:01:16,353 --> 00:01:18,186
You need to work
on your flexibility.

33
00:01:18,188 --> 00:01:19,604
(laughing): I don't remember
asking you

34
00:01:19,606 --> 00:01:21,922
to be my personal
physical therapist.

35
00:01:21,924 --> 00:01:23,775
Okay.
Okay.

36
00:01:23,777 --> 00:01:25,727
Slightly back, that's it.
Okay.

37
00:01:25,729 --> 00:01:29,030
Careful.

38
00:01:29,032 --> 00:01:30,365
You know, the first time
I got shot in Afghanistan,

39
00:01:30,367 --> 00:01:31,616
I couldn't sleep for months.

40
00:01:31,618 --> 00:01:35,036
Yeah, it's like
I'm sleepwalking.

41
00:01:35,038 --> 00:01:36,437
I can't do anything,

42
00:01:36,439 --> 00:01:38,039
and they've got me
on restrictive duty

43
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:41,242
until I am physically
and emotionally up to par.

44
00:01:41,244 --> 00:01:42,660
(phone ringing)

45
00:01:42,662 --> 00:01:45,663
And, again.

46
00:01:45,665 --> 00:01:47,415
You want to
answer that?

47
00:01:47,417 --> 00:01:50,651
Uh, no, it's okay.
I'll call her back.

48
00:01:50,653 --> 00:01:53,087
Ah, it's Alex.

49
00:01:53,089 --> 00:01:55,173
Really, Vincent,
it's okay.

50
00:01:55,175 --> 00:01:57,141
I don't mind.

51
00:01:57,143 --> 00:01:59,010
Uh, okay, thanks.

52
00:01:59,012 --> 00:02:00,478
Oh...

53
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:06,401
Look, uh...

54
00:02:06,403 --> 00:02:07,819
Catherine,
the thing is...

55
00:02:07,821 --> 00:02:09,303
You... you don't
have to explain.

56
00:02:09,305 --> 00:02:11,406
She was your fiancée.

57
00:02:11,408 --> 00:02:14,942
You were planning
a life together for years.

58
00:02:14,944 --> 00:02:16,561
Six years
and an entire childhood.

59
00:02:18,414 --> 00:02:21,115
But... you and me...

60
00:02:21,117 --> 00:02:23,000
You and I are...

61
00:02:23,002 --> 00:02:24,786
You know,
I don't know what were are.

62
00:02:24,788 --> 00:02:26,320
We're kind of in no-man's-land.

63
00:02:26,322 --> 00:02:29,257
Yeah, I mean-I mean, we've
hardly even known each other,

64
00:02:29,259 --> 00:02:30,925
what, a few months.

65
00:02:34,663 --> 00:02:37,682
You know,
it's really none of my business.

66
00:02:46,358 --> 00:02:47,942
ALEX:
I'll be right out.

67
00:02:47,944 --> 00:02:50,394
Yeah.

68
00:02:50,396 --> 00:02:55,116
You know,
it's, uh, it's good you called.

69
00:02:55,118 --> 00:02:57,034
There's, um, there's something

70
00:02:57,036 --> 00:02:59,737
that I wanted to talk
to you about, too.

71
00:02:59,739 --> 00:03:02,890
ALEX: I'll be all yours
if you just give me a sec.

72
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:15,052
Is this what
you wanted to show me?

73
00:03:19,508 --> 00:03:22,477
No.

74
00:03:27,149 --> 00:03:30,017
This is.

75
00:03:32,321 --> 00:03:35,323
(frame clatters)

76
00:03:40,529 --> 00:03:43,114
How am I supposed to compete
with six years?

77
00:03:43,116 --> 00:03:45,566
Not to mention the fact
that they grew up together

78
00:03:45,568 --> 00:03:50,121
and that she doesn't know all
the darker sides of him.

79
00:03:50,123 --> 00:03:52,423
But, if I say, hey, pick me,

80
00:03:52,425 --> 00:03:54,625
and ignore that
totally perfect, caring woman

81
00:03:54,627 --> 00:03:56,460
that you planned on spending
your life with,

82
00:03:56,462 --> 00:03:58,245
I am a total bitch.

83
00:03:58,247 --> 00:03:59,797
Aren't I?

84
00:04:00,883 --> 00:04:02,600
Are you?

85
00:04:02,602 --> 00:04:04,435
Don't "are you?" me.

86
00:04:04,437 --> 00:04:06,103
It's bad enough
that I am being forced

87
00:04:06,105 --> 00:04:07,972
to come here just to
get back to full duty.

88
00:04:07,974 --> 00:04:09,690
I could do without
the self-reflective crap.

89
00:04:09,692 --> 00:04:11,258
First of all, let me say

90
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:13,060
that I am impressed
by your willingness

91
00:04:13,062 --> 00:04:14,261
to open up so quickly...

92
00:04:14,263 --> 00:04:16,364
Yes, I know
the mandatory routine.

93
00:04:16,366 --> 00:04:18,282
The sooner I spill my heart,

94
00:04:18,284 --> 00:04:20,601
the faster I get out of here.

95
00:04:20,603 --> 00:04:22,236
Second, what's mandatory,

96
00:04:22,238 --> 00:04:23,754
is for us to discuss the trauma
that you went through

97
00:04:23,756 --> 00:04:26,374
during the shooting,
not your boyfriend issues.

98
00:04:26,376 --> 00:04:27,959
Oh.

99
00:04:27,961 --> 00:04:30,077
Third, yes,
you would be.

100
00:04:30,079 --> 00:04:31,913
And that's okay.

101
00:04:31,915 --> 00:04:33,113
Sometimes in life
we need to be a bitch

102
00:04:33,115 --> 00:04:35,900
in order to get
what we need.

103
00:04:35,902 --> 00:04:37,335
And you're off to a good start.

104
00:04:37,337 --> 00:04:39,086
Sorry.

105
00:04:39,088 --> 00:04:43,090
I had enough therapy
to last a lifetime

106
00:04:43,092 --> 00:04:44,308
when my mom was killed.

107
00:04:44,310 --> 00:04:47,094
I know,
that is like throwing prime rib

108
00:04:47,096 --> 00:04:48,763
at a Rottweiler.

109
00:04:48,765 --> 00:04:50,898
Interesting choice of dog.
They're beautiful.

110
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:52,516
And dangerous.

111
00:04:52,518 --> 00:04:55,803
No offense, Doctor...

112
00:04:55,805 --> 00:04:57,822
Oh, David.

113
00:04:57,824 --> 00:04:59,490
But I don't need a shrink

114
00:04:59,492 --> 00:05:01,359
to figure out
what my problems are.

115
00:05:01,361 --> 00:05:02,944
You mean running away from

116
00:05:02,946 --> 00:05:04,986
tough emotions and throwing
yourself into your work?

117
00:05:06,081 --> 00:05:07,748
I read your file.

118
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:10,334
I hope it was a good read.
Mm-hmm.

119
00:05:10,336 --> 00:05:13,588
And from your file,
my conjecture is

120
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:15,155
you lean on
your crutches:

121
00:05:15,157 --> 00:05:17,324
work, protecting people...

122
00:05:17,326 --> 00:05:19,210
Yes, I took an oath.

123
00:05:19,212 --> 00:05:20,928
To serve and protect.

124
00:05:20,930 --> 00:05:23,130
But who are
you really protecting?

125
00:05:31,506 --> 00:05:34,475
(man speaks indistinctly
over P.A.)

126
00:05:40,532 --> 00:05:42,116
(keypad beeping)

127
00:05:58,834 --> 00:06:00,835
(zipper closing)

128
00:06:09,061 --> 00:06:11,145
Catherine?

129
00:06:12,314 --> 00:06:13,931
Alex. Hey, hi.

130
00:06:13,933 --> 00:06:15,716
What are you doing here?

131
00:06:15,718 --> 00:06:17,101
I was just jumping
through hoops.

132
00:06:17,103 --> 00:06:18,385
Had to get a final evaluation

133
00:06:18,387 --> 00:06:20,021
before they return me
to full duty.

134
00:06:20,023 --> 00:06:21,355
What are you doing?

135
00:06:21,357 --> 00:06:22,990
I'm just heading home.
Running late.

136
00:06:22,992 --> 00:06:24,358
For... the gym?

137
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:27,495
Oh, no,
it's, uh, change of clothes.

138
00:06:27,497 --> 00:06:30,581
I live a very glamorous life.

139
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:32,166
(elevator bell dings)

140
00:06:32,168 --> 00:06:33,584
Well, that's my ride.

141
00:06:33,586 --> 00:06:34,585
See you.

142
00:06:34,587 --> 00:06:37,171
Bye.

143
00:06:44,963 --> 00:06:46,547
JT:
<i>Someone please explain to me</i>

144
00:06:46,549 --> 00:06:49,967
how a guy who's unemployed,
never goes out,

145
00:06:49,969 --> 00:06:52,353
and is officially dead,
gets not one,

146
00:06:52,355 --> 00:06:55,639
but two smoking hot women
fighting for his attention.

147
00:06:55,641 --> 00:06:58,092
No, JT, the whole point
of going over there

148
00:06:58,094 --> 00:07:00,611
was to tell her
that I can't see her anymore.

149
00:07:00,613 --> 00:07:02,697
Because...

150
00:07:02,699 --> 00:07:03,948
because of Catherine.

151
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:05,733
Kind of, yeah.

152
00:07:05,735 --> 00:07:08,769
I mean,
Catherine's life has

153
00:07:08,771 --> 00:07:11,872
never been the same since
she found out about me.

154
00:07:11,874 --> 00:07:13,124
And my secret.

155
00:07:13,126 --> 00:07:14,875
Neither has yours.

156
00:07:16,294 --> 00:07:20,631
You and Catherine, you risk
so much to keep me safe.

157
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:22,800
And you don't want Alex
to take the same risks.

158
00:07:22,802 --> 00:07:24,135
No.

159
00:07:24,137 --> 00:07:26,837
Okay, but what if
I don't tell her?

160
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:27,955
Vincent.

161
00:07:27,957 --> 00:07:29,423
Look, I know what you're going
to say,

162
00:07:29,425 --> 00:07:32,810
okay, but, JT,
to have someone look at you

163
00:07:32,812 --> 00:07:35,730
and not feel like
you've got this big secret

164
00:07:35,732 --> 00:07:37,214
that they have to protect,
you know.

165
00:07:37,216 --> 00:07:39,016
Like Catherine does.

166
00:07:39,018 --> 00:07:40,634
Yeah.

167
00:07:40,636 --> 00:07:44,488
But, JT, I... I loved Alex.

168
00:07:44,490 --> 00:07:48,242
You know, we spent our whole
childhoods planning everything,

169
00:07:48,244 --> 00:07:50,494
and then... ah.

170
00:07:50,496 --> 00:07:52,279
I don't know,
I guess I got afraid.

171
00:07:52,281 --> 00:07:54,832
And you don't think
Catherine's just backing off

172
00:07:54,834 --> 00:07:57,368
because she's trying
to do the right thing?

173
00:07:59,988 --> 00:08:03,174
How did I end up
on Catherine's side of this?

174
00:08:03,176 --> 00:08:04,425
My side of what?

175
00:08:04,427 --> 00:08:07,378
All you, my friend.

176
00:08:12,017 --> 00:08:13,801
(sighs)

177
00:08:13,803 --> 00:08:16,720
What's this?

178
00:08:16,722 --> 00:08:18,222
I don't know how
to tell you this,

179
00:08:18,224 --> 00:08:20,474
but I ran into Alex
at the hospital.

180
00:08:20,476 --> 00:08:23,027
She was putting a bunch of
boxes into her duffel bag,

181
00:08:23,029 --> 00:08:27,231
and, it turns out that there
are a bunch of thefts

182
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:28,949
being reported at that ward.

183
00:08:28,951 --> 00:08:30,851
You've been spying on her?

184
00:08:30,853 --> 00:08:35,022
I followed up
on something I saw.

185
00:08:35,024 --> 00:08:36,490
Vincent,
she's stealing medicine

186
00:08:36,492 --> 00:08:38,692
and supplies from the hospital.

187
00:08:38,694 --> 00:08:40,377
You don't actually know that.

188
00:08:40,379 --> 00:08:42,863
Okay.

189
00:08:42,865 --> 00:08:46,167
You can believe me, or not,

190
00:08:46,169 --> 00:08:48,702
but there is an open
narcotics investigation

191
00:08:48,704 --> 00:08:50,370
into these thefts,

192
00:08:50,372 --> 00:08:53,257
and someone else is going
to find out,

193
00:08:53,259 --> 00:08:55,226
eventually.

194
00:08:56,812 --> 00:08:59,713
Does she know?

195
00:08:59,715 --> 00:09:03,767
I mean,
does she know how careful

196
00:09:03,769 --> 00:09:06,320
she has to be with your secret?

197
00:09:06,322 --> 00:09:07,938
No.

198
